From 10bff6ca51efecfbbc72f41bc51abe5ae96325cc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Disyer <daniel@tohka.us>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 13:01:35 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat: add self-registration with email verification and
 Cloudflare Turnstile

Replace the static "Please contact admin" registration page with a
self-registration flow: user enters email, receives an activation link,
and sets a password on the activation page. This reuses the existing
activation email infrastructure (OneTimeToken, 'registered' email
template, /user/activate page).

Add Cloudflare Turnstile captcha support alongside reCAPTCHA:
  - New TurnstileMiddleware validates turnstile tokens against
    Cloudflare's siteverify API.
  - Configured via TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY and TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY env vars.
  - Turnstile widget is rendered on the register page when configured.

Add OVERLEAF_ALLOWED_REGISTRATION_DOMAINS env var to restrict
self-registration to specific email domains (comma-separated).
When unset, registration is open to all domains.
